Defendant in custody.  
State files an Amended Information amending Count 4 from burglary - commit a battery on person to burglary of building or dwelling, contrary to Section 943.10(1m)(a) of the Wisconsin Statutes, a Class F felony.  
Count 1 of Amended Information - Second degree sexual assault - Guilty plea;
Count 4 of Amended Information - Burglary of building or dwelling - Guilty plea;
Count 5 of Amended Information - Strangulation and Suffocation - Guilty plea;
Count 7 of Amended Information - False Imprisonment - Guilty plea;
Count 9 of Amended Information - Battery - Guilty plea.  Convicted.   State moves to dismiss and read in count 2 of Amended Information, second degree sexual assault; count 3 of Amended Information, second degree sexual assault; count 6 of Amended Information, strangulation and suffocation; count 8 of Amended Information, false imprisonment; and count 10 of Amended Information, battery.   Motion granted.  Court orders a pre-sentence investigation report along with a psycho-sexual evaluation to be completed by DOC.  Report to be filed by 01-02-15.  Sentencing hearing set for 01-15-15 at 8:30 a.m.  Court orders bail to be revoked.  
Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights. 
Minutes.
